Since updating from 1.2.6.1 to 1.2.6.2 I am getting a bug when using the mk16 parachute. Once the rocket passes 6000m the center of mass suddenly shifts way below where the craft is. this makes the camera focus on a point below the rocket and makes the physics go a little crazy. I'm using a few other mods so it may be a compatibility issue. Is anyone else having this?

Hey guys, currently in the middle of the Atlantic Ocean somewhat near Cuba. I'm writing this from a snail-mail speed internet, which costs 30$/h (no worries, I took the money from donations you guys offered, I'm connected for you guys after all).

I managed to finish the update yesterday, which I was not able to push because I did not find an internet connection, so I'm taking a little time to do this now, so there you go, v1.2.6.3 is out!

Changelog:

December 27th 2014
v1.2.6.3
*Hotfix*
-Reverted the editor GUI changes which caused CoM bugs in flight
-Fixed a bug where stock chutes would not apply parachute model changes correctly
-Only lvl 1+ engineers can repack chutes anymore

This fixes the CoM related bugs, I think RealChute should be stable for a while now. If you guys find more bugs however, please don't just say "hi heres a bug", it doesn't help me at all. Strip off all mods except RealChute, repeat the bug once, close the game, and then post your output_log.txt on here for me to look at. This is the best and fastest way for me to find the issues.

Now that this is done, I'll go back to relax by the pool. I'll wish you all happy holidays once more, and a happy new year, and I'll be back in 2015

Cheers!

Chris

Quick question.

I have had to tweek scale some radial chutes down in size so I can fit an experiment or part test on the top of a Mk 1 pod.

However the radial chutes seem to be burning up in there cases at the 50 - 40km band of intense heating.

My Kerbal pilots are basic and we ride the heat zone with no SAS there is very little sway .. a few degrees outside the retrograde circle at the most.

There seems to be no difference between real chute radials and standard MK2-r radials... if I leave these at their standard size they can survive.

But I am on the edge of the 18 ton limit so much that I am dropping fuel from the tanks to keep within. And scaling the chutes down to save on mass.

Is this happening to anyone else... is there small fix perhaps?

Now that this is done, I'll go back to relax by the pool. I'll wish you all happy holidays once more, and a happy new year, and I'll be back in 2015

Cheers!

Chris

I noticed something when installing a new version of real chute today. Probably not related to the new version though.

I've always removed the MM files in RealChute to maintain stock behavior for the stock chutes, but this time I forgot it, and while loading an existing in-flight vessel with the stock radial chutes, the whole vessel started floating away from the camera after a few seconds. Might be worth looking into.

There is no message in the log that comes with this bug.

The problem is easily reproducible by installing RealChute without MM files, launching a vessel with stock chutes, quitting, adding the MM files, and loading the vessel again. It will start to float away from the camera.
